		<description>Actually, the UNIX model doesn&#039;t even require sending the password.  It&#039;s more of a challenge/response.  Server sends you a token encrypted with your password, you decrypt it and send it back (or vice versa).

You should never be sending/storing the plaintext password, even over a secure connection.  Dunno if you can do this from a browser though...</description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Actually, the UNIX model doesn&#8217;t even require sending the password.  It&#8217;s more of a challenge/response.  Server sends you a token encrypted with your password, you decrypt it and send it back (or vice versa).</p>
<p>You should never be sending/storing the plaintext password, even over a secure connection.  Dunno if you can do this from a browser though&#8230;</p>
]]></content:encoded>
